eNCA's Devan Murugan has more details. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The government has announced that it will extend the temporary reduction in the general fuel levy. The relief of R1.50 per litre will continue through June and will be reduced to 75c per litre in July. The relief falls away in August. Meanwhile, the Minerals Resources and Energy Department announced an adjustment to the fuel prices effective from midnight. The price of 93 octane petrol will increase by R2.43c a litre and 95 octane petrol will be going up by R2.33c a litre. Diesel will increase by R1.10c The price of illuminating paraffin will increase by R1.56c a litre. Watch the video above for more details on this story. eNCA's Devan Murugan has more details. Courtesy #DStv403  Joint Statement-extension of the Temporary Reduction in the General Fuel Levy by eNCA.com on Scribd  Media Statement - Fuel Prices for Jun 2022 by eNCA.com on Scribd 